          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-05-26T14:54:41Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Transparency Requirements Aimed at Congressional Expenditures Act or the TRACE Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires a Member of Congress, spouse of a Member, or employee of Congress to submit a financial disclosure if a business that they own or control receives a loan under the Paycheck Protection Program for small businesses affected by COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019). The disclosure must include the name and address of the recipient's place of business and the amount of the loan.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-06-22T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
